message.content:
Below is one worked‐through solution that matches the two assembled “tower” and “animal‐like” figures exactly as shown, without re‐orienting any of the Dictionary blocks.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1)  ANALYSIS OF THE MAIN TARGET IMAGE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
•  Overall there are two separate builds:

  A)  Left “Animal‐like” Figure (8 blocks total):
     –  Bottom layer is a short yellow block supporting
        a red “cradle” block.  
     –  Above the red cradle sits one small green block.
     –  Two blue cubes sit side by side on top, forming
        a “head” or “ears.”  
     –  Off to one side of the red block are another short
        yellow block plus two orange triangular wedges
        arranged like “wings” or fins.
  
  B)  Right “Tower” (8 blocks total):
     –  Bottom layer is a short yellow block (horizontal).
     –  Two red ring‐blocks are stacked to create a tall
        circular window in the center.
     –  Another short yellow block spans the top of those
        red rings as a “platform.”
     –  Two tall green pillars sit on that platform.
     –  A third short yellow block bridges across the
        tops of the green pillars.
     –  Finally, an orange triangular wedge perches on
        top as a roof.

•  Layer/Block Count:
  –  Left structure uses 8 blocks in about four layers.
  –  Right structure uses 8 blocks in about four layers.
  –  In total, 16 blocks are visible.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2)  SELECTING BLOCKS FROM THE DICTIONARY
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Matching each shape/color/orientation exactly (no rotation):

LEFT “ANIMAL‐LIKE” FIGURE (8 blocks)  
  •  1 × #8  (yellow, short rectangular) as the base  
  •  1 × #2  (red cradle‐shaped block)  
  •  1 × #6  (green, small rectangular)  
  •  2 × #4  (blue cubes)  
  •  1 × #8  (another yellow, short rectangular)  
  •  1 × #13 (orange triangular wedge)  
  •  1 × #14 (orange triangular wedge)

RIGHT “TOWER” (8 blocks)  
  •  1 × #8  (yellow, short rectangular) for the bottom  
  •  2 × #3  (red ring block), stacked  
  •  1 × #8  (yellow, short rectangular) as mid‐platform  
  •  2 × #7  (tall green pillars)  
  •  1 × #8  (yellow, short rectangular) bridging top  
  •  1 × #16 (orange triangular wedge) for roof

In total:  
  –  #2 × 1  
  –  #3 × 2  
  –  #4 × 2  
  –  #6 × 1  
  –  #7 × 2  
  –  #8 × 5  (used repeatedly for all yellow horizontal beams)  
  –  #13 × 1  
  –  #14 × 1  
  –  #16 × 1  

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3)  STEP‐BY‐STEP ASSEMBLY ORDER
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Below is one logical bottom‐to‐top sequence for building
both structures:

{
  Step1:  Move block with index 8   //Left base
  Step2:  Move block with index 2   //Red cradle on left
  Step3:  Move block with index 6   //Green block on cradle
  Step4:  Move block with index 4   //Blue cube #1 on top
  Step5:  Move block with index 4   //Blue cube #2 on top
  Step6:  Move block with index 8   //2nd yellow block (side piece)
  Step7:  Move block with index 13  //Orange wedge (left wing)
  Step8:  Move block with index 14  //Orange wedge (right wing)
  Step9:  Move block with index 8   //Right tower’s bottom
  Step10: Move block with index 3   //1st red ring
  Step11: Move block with index 3   //2nd red ring
  Step12: Move block with index 8   //Mid‐level yellow beam
  Step13: Move block with index 7   //1st tall green pillar
  Step14: Move block with index 7   //2nd tall green pillar
  Step15: Move block with index 8   //Top yellow beam
  Step16: Move block with index 16  //Orange roof wedge
}

That completes the structures exactly as pictured.
